{"article_id":"pqffI52SPn1TxOWV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate Republicans may be all over the map on an Obamacare repeal plan ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"but on one fundamental point","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"- reducing insurance premiums -","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"they are in danger","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"of overpromising","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"and underdelivering .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"The reality is they have only a few ways","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"to reduce Americans ' premiums :","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"Offer consumers bigger subsidies .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Allow insurers to offer skimpier coverage .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"Or permit insurers to charge more","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"- usually much more -","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"to those with pre-existing illnesses and who are older","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"and tend to rack up the biggest bills .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Since there ' s no appetite within the GOP","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"for throwing more taxpayer money at the problem ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"Republicans will need to make some hard decisions","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"to hit their goal .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"But the effort","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"to drive down premium prices","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"will inevitably create a new set of winners and losers","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"and complicate leadership ' s path to the 50 votes","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"they need","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"to fulfill their seven-year promise","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"to repeal Obamacare .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"\" Anyone can figure out how to reduce premiums , \"","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"said Sen. Chris Murphy","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"( D-Conn. ) .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"\" You can reduce premiums","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"by kicking everybody","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that has a pre-existing condition","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"off insurance","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"or dramatically reducing benefits . \"","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Republicans say","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"that Obamacare ' s insurance regulations are responsible","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"for making coverage prohibitively expensive","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"and contend","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"that premiums would fall","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"if those rules are rolled back .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"They say","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"they have multiple ideas","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"about how to roll those back","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"while also insulating the most vulnerable","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"but have yet to weave those together into actual legislation .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Pulse newsletter","depth":3},{"id":45,"text":"Get the latest on the health care fight , every weekday morning","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"- in your inbox .","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"Email Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"By signing up","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"You can unsubscribe at any time .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"\" We can overcomplicate it , \"","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"said Sen. Thom Tillis","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"( R-N.C. )","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"said of reducing premiums .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"\" But at the end of the day , does it make sense for a family","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"that ' s trying to get health care ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"trying to pay for their insurance ? \"","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"The reality may not be so straightforward :","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"Just ask ex-President Barack Obama ,","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"who promised","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"that his health care overhaul would save families $ 2,500","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"and that consumers would be able to keep their doctor or insurance plan","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"if they wanted .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"In the decades before Obamacare , premiums were also rising nearly every year","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"as a result of the introduction of expensive new drugs and procedures , as well as medical tests .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"Those factors are likely to continue to push up health care costs in a post-Obamacare world ,","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"not to mention that insurers are the ones","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"who actually price the coverage","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"and set rates each year .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Analysts say","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"Republicans might achieve their goal for younger , healthier consumers ,","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"but at the cost","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"of wiping out popular consumer safeguards like the ban","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"on insurers","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"charging more for coverage to those with pre-existing conditions .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"That , in turn , could leave millions unable to afford the hikes","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"associated with heart disease or rheumatoid arthritis or cancer .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"The Congressional Budget Office ' s report on the House repeal plan also made the task of Senate Republicans more difficult .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"The analysis concluded","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"that allowing states","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"to opt out of Obamacare ' s pre-existing condition requirement would destabilize markets","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"and in some cases , drive premiums upward for older , sicker people .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Several Republican sources say","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"the CBO ' s assessment would encourage lawmakers to preserve Obamacare ' s pre-existing condition policy .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"Not everyone is convinced .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Sen. Ron Johnson","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"( R-Wis. )","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"Obamacare ' s pre-existing condition policy is the \" biggest reason \"","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"premiums have gone up .","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"\" A lot of people don ' t want to touch that , \"","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"Johnson said of his fellow Republicans .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"\" I would like to .","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"Because I think","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"you can handle pre-existing conditions in a different way","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"without collapsing markets . \"","depth":15},{"id":97,"text":"Most Republicans do support allowing insurers to sell more basic and , therefore , cheaper policies","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"without , say , maternity coverage , mental health or prescription drug benefits .","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"They argue","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"that consumers should be able to buy more basic","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"- and inexpensive -","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"policies","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"tailored to their specific needs .","depth":15},{"id":104,"text":"The problem is , they may not be able to make such changes under the complex rules","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"governing the fast-track process","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"being used","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"to avoid a Democratic filibuster .","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"Some Republicans also support allowing insurers to charge older people higher premiums","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"despite the likely political blowback ,","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"although Republican leaders appear to have been spooked by the storm","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"House Republicans faced","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"when they raised the idea .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Ultimately , the GOP drive","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"to reduce premiums","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"could wind up expanding the number of uninsured Americans .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"The CBO also estimated","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"that the House repeal bill ,","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"which would scrap many insurance regulations ,","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"would result in 23 million more uninsured Americans by 2026 than under the Affordable Care Act .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"Premiums vary all over the country","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"but have generally been on the rise .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"This year , benchmark Obamacare policies in 17 major cities rose an average of 9 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"according to the nonpartisan Kaiser Family Foundation .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"That ' s up from 2 percent in 2016 .","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"There also have been eye-popping rate increases in Obamacare plans","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"- in some places , doubling in one year .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"while lawmakers can tweak market conditions in the hope","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"of making premiums fall ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"they don ' t control how insurers set rates .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"\" If it were easy ,","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"it would have been done last week , \"","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"said Sen. Mike Rounds","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"( R-S.D . ) ,","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"who was an insurance executive","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"before he ran for public office .","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"\" The real challenge for us is recognizing how you bring the actual cost back down","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"and transfer the cost to a willing business community , \"","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"referring to insurance companies .","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"Rounds said","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"the GOP can drive down premiums","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"by eliminating Obamacare requirements such as mandates on how much of the health care expenses a plan has to cover","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"and age bands","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"that prevent insurers from charging older people more than three times what younger people pay .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"\" In the end , reducing cost is going to be ultimately the way","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"\" the bill is judged ,","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"said Sen. John Thune of South Dakota , the Senate ' s No . 3 Republican .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"When asked","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"whether that ' s going to be possible ,","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"Thune said ,","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"\" That is the goal . \"","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"Republicans , mindful of the Democrats ' experience","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"when Obamacare was enacted in 2010 ,","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"have been careful not to put a dollar figure on how much premiums will decline .","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"\" The thing","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"we ' ll be judged by","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"is the extent","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"to which we ' ve overcome the promises of the Obama administration , \"","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"said Sen. Chuck Grassley of Iowa , a top Republican on the Senate Finance Committee ,","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"enumerating promises","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"Democrats made about Obamacare","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"that didn ' t pan out ,","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"including falling premiums and consumers being able to maintain their care arrangements .","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"\" The bottom line , \"","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"he said ,","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"\" is we need to make sure what we can do","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"to make sure","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"that that doesn ' t happen again . \"","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":339,"left":213,"right":338,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":21